Plan written to `plans/node-ci-github-actions.plan.md`.

It covers 6 steps: initialize package.json, install dev deps (vitest + eslint), create ESLint flat config, pin Node 20 in `.nvmrc`, add minimal src/test files, and write the `.github/workflows/ci.yml` workflow.

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The workflow triggers on both `push` and `pull_request` -- this matters because PRs from forks don't trigger `push` events on the upstream repo, so omitting `pull_request` would leave fork-based PRs unchecked.
- Separating `npm run lint` and `npm test` as distinct `run` steps (rather than one combined script) gives GitHub Actions separate pass/fail annotations and makes it immediately obvious in the UI whether it was a lint failure or a test failure.
- Step 5 (trivial src/test files) is a real prerequisite -- Vitest exits non-zero when it finds no test files, which would permanently fail CI until real tests are added.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

